WEBVTT

00:00.908 --> 00:03.455
Margarita on the rocks, huh? What?

00:03.528 --> 00:05.495
That's an excellent
choice, eh...

00:05.530 --> 00:07.363
(Glass shattering)

00:11.770 --> 00:12.818
Have you seen our wine list?

00:14.422 --> 00:16.789
Oh my God, what happened
to all the bottles?

00:16.825 --> 00:18.691
Danny. Pfft.

00:18.693 --> 00:20.710
I'll talk to him, man.

00:20.762 --> 00:22.779
Thank you, so much for filling in, man.

00:22.831 --> 00:24.697
I can't believe I forgot
to do the schedule again.

00:24.733 --> 00:26.633
It's all my mom's
fault she's so selfish.

00:26.668 --> 00:28.434
Had to go on her stupid honeymoon.

00:29.604 --> 00:31.454
Who's gonna wait on all these tables?

00:31.490 --> 00:32.572
- Hey.
- Riley, hey.

00:32.607 --> 00:34.474
- Perfect timing.
- Is Danny ready to go?

00:34.509 --> 00:36.426
Yes, as soon as he
finishes cooking this order.

00:36.461 --> 00:37.393
What order?

00:37.429 --> 00:39.445
Hi, thank you guys for
waiting, this is Riley.

00:39.447 --> 00:40.747
She'll be your server this evening.

00:40.799 --> 00:42.398
Push the appies.

00:42.434 --> 00:43.816
You know what, Ben?
Ben, push them yourself.

00:43.818 --> 00:46.686
All right? I passed the bar so
that I wouldn't have to work in one.

00:46.721 --> 00:48.821
Come on, dude, you've
got to get it together.

00:48.874 --> 00:50.740
I mean, Tucker's making drinks?

00:50.775 --> 00:52.692
What's next? Is Emma
working the deep fryer?

00:52.727 --> 00:54.744
You kidding? She's my
best cocktail waitress.

00:59.551 --> 01:01.501
(Theme music playing)

01:01.553 --> 01:04.587
♪ It's amazing how the unexpected ♪

01:04.638 --> 01:07.282
♪ can take your life
and change directions ♪

01:07.382 --> 01:11.223
- Sync and corrected by <font color="829ee0">TheDelta</font> -
- www.Addic7ed.Com -

01:11.680 --> 01:14.564
man, finding a new manager for the bar
is going to be harder than I thought.

01:14.599 --> 01:16.599
No one included the
photo with their resume.

01:16.651 --> 01:18.518
How am I supposed to tell if she's hot?

01:19.688 --> 01:21.571
And why are you eating
everything in the house?

01:21.606 --> 01:22.605
Didn't you just eat at Riley's?

01:22.657 --> 01:24.691
That's the problem.
She's a horrible cook.

01:24.693 --> 01:27.527
Oh. I know.

01:27.579 --> 01:28.695
She make you one of her meat waffles?

01:30.532 --> 01:31.698
Yeah. I didn't know it was possible

01:31.700 --> 01:33.583
for something to be both overcooked

01:33.618 --> 01:34.701
and undercooked at the exact same time.

01:36.705 --> 01:38.588
But I don't want to hurt her feelings,

01:38.623 --> 01:39.706
so, everything she puts in front of me,

01:39.758 --> 01:41.708
I've been tossing, hiding, or flushing.

01:42.794 --> 01:44.594
Knock, knock. Hey, babe.

01:44.629 --> 01:46.629
Oh, hey, honey. Um...

01:46.681 --> 01:48.548
Now that we've got all the food out,

01:48.600 --> 01:49.716
we can finally clean the fridge.

01:51.636 --> 01:52.635
Clean it, Ben.

01:54.723 --> 01:56.606
Um, you forgot your gym bag,

01:56.641 --> 01:58.641
and I found a meat waffle in it.

01:58.693 --> 02:01.561
Oh, yeah, they're just so good

02:01.563 --> 02:03.646
that I wanted to save
one for after practice.

02:03.698 --> 02:05.531
They taste even better when they've

02:05.567 --> 02:07.567
been in a hot locker for a while.

02:07.619 --> 02:08.701
No way!

02:08.737 --> 02:10.652
I just got a resume from Sam Saffe.

02:10.705 --> 02:11.704
I think it's really her.

02:11.740 --> 02:14.574
Wait, wait, wait, Samantha
Saffe from high school?

02:14.626 --> 02:16.576
Ugh, she was so perfect.

02:16.628 --> 02:17.660
God, I hated her.

02:19.581 --> 02:20.630
Really? I thought she was nice.

02:22.667 --> 02:23.716
You know, now that I think about it,

02:23.752 --> 02:25.501
not a huge fan.

02:26.588 --> 02:28.588
Yeah, well, I loved her.

02:28.640 --> 02:30.640
Sat behind her in home
room for three years.

02:30.675 --> 02:33.593
Smell of cherry lip balm and
acne cream still gets me going.

02:34.763 --> 02:36.596
She didn't even know you were alive.

02:36.648 --> 02:38.648
Oh, she will now.

02:38.683 --> 02:40.767
Wait, you're not really
gonna have her come in

02:40.769 --> 02:41.768
for an interview, are you?

02:41.770 --> 02:43.653
Uh, hell yeah.

02:43.688 --> 02:44.687
This is the kind of moment

02:44.739 --> 02:46.572
you dream about your entire life.

02:46.608 --> 02:47.774
I'm gonna let her
think she's got the job,

02:47.776 --> 02:49.659
and then I'm gonna yank it away.

02:49.694 --> 02:52.612
Then she'll feel like I did
every single day of my life.

02:52.664 --> 02:56.699
And that, my friends, will
be the ultimate "re-Benge."

02:57.786 --> 02:58.718
Ha-ha!

02:58.753 --> 03:00.520
How have I not used that before?

03:00.555 --> 03:02.555
"Re-Benge"...
That's genius.

03:04.476 --> 03:08.461
Oh, these are the moments where I
really feel like I dodged a bullet.

03:11.349 --> 03:12.332
- Hey.
- Hey, Riles.

03:13.501 --> 03:15.351
Back from my honeymoon.

03:15.403 --> 03:16.703
Wanna see my tan lines?

03:16.738 --> 03:18.338
Trick question. I don't have any.

03:19.691 --> 03:22.659
Yeah, yeah, I got that
from your postcard.

03:22.711 --> 03:25.778
Even though the post office
blacked out all the nude parts.

03:25.830 --> 03:28.598
Sounds like your honeymoon
was a dream come true.

03:28.633 --> 03:29.732
Yeah. Sort of.

03:29.768 --> 03:31.668
I want a divorce.

03:31.703 --> 03:33.469
What?

03:33.505 --> 03:34.687
You just got married!

03:34.689 --> 03:36.589
You and Brad seem so happy together.

03:36.624 --> 03:39.392
Well, of course Brad was happy.

03:39.427 --> 03:40.376
He was with me!

03:41.429 --> 03:43.429
But, you know, then on
the plane on the way home,

03:43.465 --> 03:45.465
I realized something terrible:

03:45.500 --> 03:48.768
He was coming home with me.

03:48.803 --> 03:51.788
I had breakfast, he was there.

03:51.823 --> 03:53.806
I had lunch, still there.

03:53.808 --> 03:55.792
Dinner, bed, my 2:00 A.M. tinkle time,

03:55.844 --> 03:57.593
there, there, there!

03:57.629 --> 04:00.580
And he's just completely smothering me.

04:00.582 --> 04:04.567
Or... loving you?

04:04.602 --> 04:05.551
(Phone buzzes)

04:05.587 --> 04:06.552
Ugh.

04:06.554 --> 04:09.589
He's left me 10 messages
already this morning,

04:09.624 --> 04:12.408
and I just saw him last night.

04:12.444 --> 04:13.526
(Intercom beeps)

04:13.561 --> 04:16.312
Mrs. Perrin, there's a
Brad Walker here to see you.

04:16.346 --> 04:18.380
Oh my God, Brad? Brad!
What is Brad doing here?

04:18.416 --> 04:19.682
Who knows?

04:19.718 --> 04:22.702
He probably planted a GPS in my bra.

04:22.737 --> 04:24.754
Okay, all right, here's what you do.

04:24.789 --> 04:26.639
Just feel him out and see

04:26.674 --> 04:28.658
if he'll be completely
crushed if I leave him.

04:28.710 --> 04:30.760
Oh, who am I kidding,
of course he will be.

04:30.795 --> 04:32.712
Why would I do that?

04:32.747 --> 04:35.565
I gave you two sons. You owe me.

04:38.586 --> 04:41.437
Yo, Sam's gonna be here any minute.

04:41.489 --> 04:43.456
This is gonna be epic. I'm
not even gonna recognize her.

04:43.458 --> 04:47.493
She's gonna be all like, "oh, my
God, Ben Wheeler, is that you?"

04:47.495 --> 04:50.346
And then I'll be all like, "I'm
sorry, do we know each other?"

04:50.398 --> 04:52.832
And then she'll be like, "it's
me, Sam Saffe from homeroom."

04:52.867 --> 04:54.383
And I'll be like, "oh, what's up, baby?"

04:54.436 --> 04:55.768
Oh, here she is.

04:55.804 --> 04:57.720
Crap. She's even hotter.

04:57.756 --> 04:59.739
Okay. Tucker, follow my lead.

04:59.774 --> 05:05.495
And another thing. If I ever catch
you stealing... olives ever again,

05:05.530 --> 05:06.579
you're fired.

05:06.614 --> 05:07.647
'Cause I'm the owner of this bar.

05:07.682 --> 05:10.500
Yeah, that's right, I own this bar.

05:12.487 --> 05:13.553
Look, I'm sorry, man.

05:21.479 --> 05:23.329
It's not gonna happen again.

05:25.767 --> 05:27.366
Hi, I'm Sam.

05:27.368 --> 05:28.718
I'm here about the manager position.

05:28.753 --> 05:30.603
I'm guessing you're the owner.

05:30.605 --> 05:32.572
Right, hi, Sam.

05:32.624 --> 05:34.607
Why don't we... why don't
we sit down over here?

05:37.662 --> 05:40.480
I'm... I'm Ben.

05:40.515 --> 05:42.515
Nice to meet you.

05:42.567 --> 05:45.635
Uh, so, I think my resume is
up to date with my work history.

05:45.670 --> 05:47.487
Ben Wheeler.

05:47.522 --> 05:49.422
Right. Got it.

05:49.457 --> 05:52.525
Uh, and as you can see, I have a degree in hotel
restaurant management.

05:52.560 --> 05:54.393
I'm sorry, let me stop you right there.

05:54.429 --> 05:56.779
Is it just me, or do
I look familiar to you?

05:56.815 --> 05:59.398
No, I don't think so.

05:59.434 --> 06:01.734
Uh, I have been working
in this industry for...

06:01.769 --> 06:03.719
It's me! Ben!

06:03.755 --> 06:06.689
Ben Wheeler. We went
to high school together?

06:06.724 --> 06:08.574
We did?

06:08.610 --> 06:10.693
I sat behind you in
homeroom for three years.

06:10.745 --> 06:13.396
You did?

06:13.431 --> 06:15.498
I only remember some
annoying guy with braces.

06:19.420 --> 06:21.454
Oh, my God, it is you!

06:21.506 --> 06:24.357
Danny Wheeler's little brother!

06:25.476 --> 06:28.327
How is he?

06:29.697 --> 06:31.731
Well, after the utter
bliss of my honeymoon...

06:31.766 --> 06:33.666
Yeah, Brad, about that.

06:33.701 --> 06:36.736
What if I had some news
that wasn't so blissful?

06:36.771 --> 06:40.473
Oh, great. Just pile it on, life.

06:40.475 --> 06:42.575
Take another swing at
the ol' Brad punching bag.

06:42.577 --> 06:45.478
How much can one man lose in one day?

06:45.513 --> 06:47.513
Oh...

06:47.549 --> 06:49.382
- So, you know?
- Of course I know!

06:49.434 --> 06:50.550
I know that he was so
young and full of life,

06:50.602 --> 06:52.318
with the whole
world right at his...

06:52.370 --> 06:53.519
Wait, how did you find
out that my brother died?

06:53.555 --> 06:56.389
Tad's dead? Oh, my God!

06:56.441 --> 06:58.691
I... I obviously
had no idea.

06:58.726 --> 07:01.611
But... you seemed so upset,

07:01.663 --> 07:03.296
I just assumed.

07:03.331 --> 07:04.680
You assumed that my brother was dead?

07:06.668 --> 07:08.467
I'm a really good assumer.

07:09.704 --> 07:11.537
I got the call this morning.

07:11.539 --> 07:13.522
Bonnie already slipped out of bed.

07:13.558 --> 07:15.524
She's so sweet not to wake me.

07:15.560 --> 07:19.312
I'm the executor of the will,
that's why I came to see you.

07:20.398 --> 07:22.348
That's just... ugh,
that's horrible.

07:22.383 --> 07:23.349
I can't believe it.

07:23.384 --> 07:25.401
Tad's dead.

07:25.453 --> 07:26.402
What are you doing?

07:26.454 --> 07:28.754
I'm a big note taker.

07:30.358 --> 07:32.692
He was on a spiritual
quest around the world

07:32.727 --> 07:33.759
to find himself.

07:33.795 --> 07:36.629
Sadly, he did...

07:36.664 --> 07:38.731
At the bottom of a
ravine in Machu Picchu!

07:38.783 --> 07:43.603
I begged him not to text and
hang glide at the same time!

07:44.622 --> 07:46.505
Oh, hey, Brad.

07:46.557 --> 07:47.640
There you are.

07:47.675 --> 07:49.609
I just got your messages about Tad.

07:49.644 --> 07:51.544
I am so sorry.

07:51.546 --> 07:52.545
- Oh, Bon-Bon.
- Okay.

07:52.597 --> 07:54.397
You're all I have left.

07:54.449 --> 07:56.465
I am never gonna let you go.

07:56.501 --> 07:58.434
Aww...

07:58.486 --> 07:59.785
Never say never.

